{
  "texts": [
    "The Critic module also contains a memory M 𝐶 to store previous experiences.",
    "Inspired by the A2C algorithm, we utilize the advantage value 𝑣 𝑛 of action 𝑎 𝑛 in the given state 𝑠 𝑛 as the measurement.In particular, Critic takes the state 𝑠 𝑛, action 𝑎 𝑛, and the history trajectory H 1...𝑛-1 as inputs and then outputs the advantage 𝑣 𝑛 with the experiences in M 𝐶 as references, which can be abstracted as follows:𝑣 𝑛 = Critic(𝑠 𝑛, 𝑎 𝑛; M 𝐶).",
    "(12)To compute advantage values, similar to A2C, we first estimate the state-value function 𝑉 (𝑠 𝑛), and then, based on it, we use the advantage function [33] to determine the advantage value: • Estimating state-value.",
    "The function 𝑉 (𝑠 𝑛) provides an estimation of the value of being in state 𝑠 𝑛 when following the Actor policy.",
    "We directly model the function with the LLM of the Critic module."
  ]
}